tourBios.carHigh:
Won 28 times on the GolfSlinger.com Tour from 2006-12. 

2012: Advanced to the final stage of the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament on his second try (2009) and earned conditional status on the Web.com Tour, with a T133 finish in California. 

2011: Made one start on the Web.com Tour, missing the cut at The Rex Hospital Open...Made 12 starts on the eGolf Tour, with his best result a T4 at The Grand Harbor Open. 

2010: Made PGA TOUR debut at the John Deere Classic after successfully making it through Monday qualifying...Made Web.com Tour debut at the Miccosukee Championship, where he missed the cut.
tourBios.personal: Attended Francis Lewis High School in Queens, N.Y...Favorite pro team is the New York Yankees...Always has a protein shake in his golf bag...Would like to appear in GQ magazine as he loves fashion...Biggest thrill in golf was making it to the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament...Favorite hobby is working out...Enjoys Italian and Korean food...Favorite athletes are Michael Jordan and Mike Tyson...Dream pairing would include Arnold Palmer, Ben Hogan, Seve Ballesteros and his dad...Favorite course he has played is Bethpage Black...Augusta National is No. 1 on his list of courses he'd like to play.
